<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[264,1325,284,670]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[312,414,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
: Though externally appears similar to other species of 
<emphasis box="[1063,1239,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1130,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Varta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1141,1239,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida">V. bifida</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
differs from them in having very distinctive aedeagus. It lacks the unpaird ventral apical process, and the dorsal bladelike ridge and the shaft is evenly curved rather than sinuate.
</paragraph>
